From 51e0c491b2ff1ff2770284b2df58285bea7f6796 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Copilot Agent <copilot@example.com>
Date: Wed, 6 May 2026 19:04:34 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] crypto: substitute aws-lc-rs with SymCrypt as the rustls
 provider

Backport of the SymCrypt substitution onto v1.1.0 (commit d204f9ce).

This commit swaps the cryptographic backend used by agentgateway from
aws-lc-rs to Microsoft's SymCrypt, end-to-end:

  * The rustls TLS provider is supplied by `rustls-symcrypt` instead of
    `rustls::crypto::aws_lc_rs::default_provider()`.  All cipher suite
    constants in `crates/agentgateway/src/transport/tls.rs` now come
    from `rustls_symcrypt`.
  * The direct `aws_lc_rs::aead::*` AES-256-GCM use in
    `crates/agentgateway/src/http/sessionpersistence.rs` has been replaced
    with `symcrypt::gcm::GcmExpandedKey`.  The on-disk format
    (`nonce(12) || ciphertext || tag(16)`) is preserved.
  * `aws_lc_rs::digest::SHA256` in `crates/agentgateway/src/http/oidc/{callback,session}.rs`
    has been replaced with `symcrypt::hash::sha256`.
  * `aws_lc_rs::constant_time::verify_slices_are_equal` has been replaced
    with the well-vetted `subtle::ConstantTimeEq` trait.
  * `crates/agentgateway/tests/common/hbone_server.rs` now installs the
    SymCrypt provider as the global default for the test process.

Workspace `Cargo.toml` changes:

  * `aws-lc-rs` workspace dependency removed (commented out for traceability).
  * `rustls`, `tokio-rustls`: drop the `aws_lc_rs` feature.  Both are
    configured as `default-features = false, features = ["tls12", ...]`,
    leaving the application to install the SymCrypt provider explicitly.
  * `jsonwebtoken`: switch backend from `aws_lc_rs` to the pure-Rust
    `rust_crypto` backend (with `use_pem` re-enabled so PEM helpers like
    `EncodingKey::from_ec_pem` remain available).
  * `rcgen`: switch backend from `aws_lc_rs` to `ring` (rcgen does not
    expose a SymCrypt feature; this is a pure-Rust alternative).
  * Add `rustls-symcrypt = { version = "0.2.3", features = ["chacha", "x25519"] }`,
    `symcrypt = "0.5"`, and `subtle = "2.6"`.

Notes specific to v1.1.0:

  * v1.1.0's `tls.rs` does not yet expose a `KeyExchangeGroup` enum or
    a `provider_with_options` function (those landed post-v1.1.0).  The
    substitution therefore only needs to swap cipher-suite and provider
    references; no kx-group plumbing changes are required.  Likewise,
    `crates/agentgateway/src/types/agent_xds.rs` does not reference any
    crypto types on v1.1.0, so it is left untouched.

Caveats:

  * `rustls-symcrypt` requires the SymCrypt native library to be present
    at build and run time.  The plain `symcrypt` package on Debian/Ubuntu
    ships the bare library *without* the FIPS / entropy bootstrap module
    that `SymCryptRandom` depends on.  Code paths that exercise the
    SymCrypt DRBG (AES-GCM nonce generation, OIDC encode/decode round-
    trips) will segfault at runtime in that environment, even though
    everything compiles.  Azure Linux 3 and Windows ship the full
    module and work out of the box.  The new round-trip test for the AES
    encoder is therefore gated behind `#[ignore]` with a comment that
    explains how to enable it.
